ABOUT

Curious about me?

My name is Hien Anh (Annie) Tran. I grew up in Hanoi, Vietnam, and I'm currently studying in the United States, pursuing a double major in Business Analytics and Communication with a minor in Design studies. I'm passionate about turning complex data into visually engaging insights, developing innovative marketing campaigns, and managing social media with a strategic eye. My interests also extend to UX/ UI design and creating pixel-perfect illustrations. that blend precision with creativity. I am eager to transform data into insights, and insights into strategy

My MBTI is ENFJ-A (Extraverted, Intuitive, Feeling, and Judging traits). I am very much an inspiring optimists, readily taking action to do what I feel is right. Of course, I enjoy working on projects end to end, from ideation all the way to development.

On campus, I participate in:

  • Alpha Chi Omega
  • Speaking & Listening Consultant
  • Vietnamese Student Association
  • Honor Scholar Program (2022)

    • I have a mission...

    My mission is to leverage my skills in data analytics and using them to support marketing strategies with pleasant designs. I aim to contribute to the community by sharing knowledge, collaborating on innovative projects, dealing with complex challenges, and continuously improving my vision.

    BUSINESS ANALYTICS WORKS

    Highlighted projects and insights

    Retail Analysis on Large Dataset

    The project involves analyzing retail transactional data to segment customers using the RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) approach. RFM is a marketing analysis tool that identifies a firm's best clients based on their spending habits

    #Tableau #DataVisualization #HealthcareData #HistoricalData #PublicHealth

    Housing Price Market

    Using OLS Model as a new approach for the prediction of housing prices

    #MultipleLinearRegression #MachineLearning #OLS #PredictionAnalysis

    Exploratory Data Analysis for Asset Price Analysis*

    Analyzing the performance of four stocks: S&P (SPY), Tesla (TSLA), General Motors (GM), and Apple (AAPL). The goal is to assist in selecting a stock or portfolio that can outperform the market while maintaining a reasonable level of risk. The analysis includes an overview of the dataset, graphical interpretations, and a recommended investment strategy based on the findings

    #GoogleColab #PythonLibraries #StockMarket #Finance #InvestmentStraegy

    Concert Ticket Sales

    Using Python Libraries to analyze ticket sales in Taylor Swift and Beyonce's concerts

    #GoogleColab #PythonLibraries #SalesAnalysis

    Redbull On-Premise Sale

    This project aims to analyze Red Bull account sales data using Excel to track progress and present key insights to the team

    #Excel #PivotTable #BusinessInsights #SalesPerformance

    Pizza Business Analysis

    Analyze key indicators for the pizza sales data to gain insights into the business performance. Tools used: MS SQL Server Studio, MS Excel

    #SQL #Excel #SalesInsights #DataDriven #PivotTable

    On-demand Delivery Service in Urban Cities

    Bike Business Analysis

    Causes of Mortality in the Crimean War

    During the Crimean War, Florence Nightingale used data visualization to reveal that most soldier deaths were due to poor hospital practices, not just battles. I recreated graphs to prove her point

    #Tableau #DataVisualization #HealthcareData #HistoricalData #PublicHealth
